<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880112-0092 </DOCNO><HL> Unit of United Technologies Gets $983.2 Million Job </HL><SO> </SO><CO> UTX BA GT LK </CO><IN> ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Army awarded the Sikorsky Aircraft unit of United Technologies Corp. a $983.2 million contract to produce UH-60 Blackhawk helicopters.    The twin-engine helicopter is used for carrying troops and equipment. The contract calls for Sikorsky, the prime contractor for the Blackhawk, to produce 252 helicopters over four years.    Boeing Co. received a $23.3 million Air Force contract for E-3A aircraft training equipment.    Goodyear Tire andamp; Rubber Co. got a $19.9 million Army contract for armored-vehicle parts.    Bath Iron Works was issued an $11.9 million Navy contract for guided-missile cruiser services.    Lockheed Corp. was given Air Force contracts totaling $11.2 million for C-130 aircraft engineering services and modifications. </TEXT></DOC>